<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">So you have a problem with Firefox not wrapping text when someone posts a long link in a page. Here's a solution, paste the little javascript snippet below into the location of a new bookmark. Then when you run across a page with this problem, hit the bookmark, the page will refresh with the lines properly wrapped.
<br />

<br />
javascript:(function() { var D = document; F(D.body); function F(n) { var u, r, c, x; if (n.nodeType == 3) { u = n.data.search(/\S{45}/); if (u >= 0) { r = n.splitText(u + 45); n.parentNode.insertBefore(D.createElement('wbr'), r); } } else if ((n.tagName != 'STYLE') && (n.tagName != 'SCRIPT')) { for (c = 0; x = n.childNodes[c]; ++c) { F(x); } } } D.body.innerHTML += ' '; })();
<br />

<br />

<br />
Basically go into the "Bookmarks" option on the top of the FF window. Choose "manage bookmarks" and create a new bookmark then paste the little javascript below. When you run into a page with long URL's that run off the page you can just click this bookmark and it'll fix it so the URL wraps properly within the page.
<br />

<br />
Example of long URL running off the page. <a href="http://www.anandtech.com/news/shownews.aspx?i=23997&ATVAR_START=1&p=1[/url]" target="_blank">http://www.anandtech.com/news/shownews.aspx?i=23997&ATVAR_START=1&p=1[/url]</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
